 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "Create task: CCE-4: Entity auto-linking at observe time — braid understands what you're talking about. CONTEXT: The agent writes 'the materialize engine...' and braid stores a flat string. With entity auto-linking, braid scans the text for known entity names (package names from bootstrap, spec IDs from prior observations, concept names) and auto-creates Ref datoms. The agent writes natural language. Braid does entity resolution. No flags, no syntax, no ceremony. RATIONALE: This is the minimum viable 'braid understands structure.' Not through NLP or embeddings (those provide SEMANTIC similarity), but through simple string matching against braid's own entity inventory. Entity links provide STRUCTURAL connections (same package mentioned); embeddings provide SEMANTIC connections (conceptually similar). Together they close 100% of DOGFOOD-2 missed connections. APPROACH: (1) In observe.rs, after computing the observation's embedding and before building the output: call entity_auto_link(store, observation_text) -> Vec<(EntityId, String)>. (2) entity_auto_link (in connections.rs or a new entity_link.rs ~150 LOC): collect all known entity idents from the store — bootstrap package entities (:pkg/*), spec elements (:spec/*), concept entities (:concept/*). For each known entity, check if its name (the part after the namespace prefix, lowercased) appears in the observation text (lowercased). If match: return (entity_id, match_name). (3) For each match, create a Ref datom in the same transaction: (observation_entity, :exploration/mentions-entity, matched_entity, tx, Assert). This is a new Many-cardinality Ref attribute: :exploration/mentions-entity. (4) When connections are scored, entity co-reference is a STRONG signal: two observations that both mention-entity the same package are connected by ground truth, not heuristic. (5) Edge case: common words that happen to match entity names (e.g., a package named 'state' matching 'state machine'). Mitigation: require match on the FULL package path segment (e.g., 'internal/state' or ':pkg/state'), not bare words. For short names (<5 chars), require the full path. For longer names (>=5 chars), bare name match is sufficient. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Observation mentioning 'materialize' auto-links to :pkg/internal-materialize (if bootstrap created it). (B) Observation mentioning 'APP-INV-019' auto-links to :spec/app-inv-019 (if spec element exists). (C) Observation mentioning no known entities creates no links (no false positives). (D) Auto-linked entities appear in the observation's datom set (queryable via :exploration/mentions-entity). (E) Short entity names (e.g., 'cli', 'state') require full path match to avoid false positives. (F) Performance: entity_auto_link completes in <5ms for stores with <1000 known entities. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/connections.rs or new entity_link.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs (new attribute). DEPENDS-ON: CCE-3 (innate schemas — so package entities and concept entities exist to link against). TRACES-TO: ADR-FOUNDATION-016 (Observation-Projection Duality — auto-linking is the morphism that connects observations to the structural model)."
